Don't leave me.

26:53.279 --> 26:55.613
Mr. Paskoff?

26:55.614 --> 26:56.906
Yeah.

26:56.907 --> 27:00.535
He didn't make it. I'm sorry.

27:00.536 --> 27:02.403
Oh.

27:04.081 --> 27:06.291
Well...

27:06.292 --> 27:11.170
I guess we tried. That
should be worth something.

27:11.171 --> 27:12.380
Yes.

27:12.381 --> 27:15.907
If you'll come with me, sir,
there are some formalities...

27:15.908 --> 27:18.185
- we have to go over.
- Formalities?

27:18.186 --> 27:21.614
Yeah. Just a couple
of questions we have...

27:22.683 --> 27:26.894
Like I told you before, I didn't know
the man. I just gave him a ride.

27:26.895 --> 27:30.189
Really? Come with me.

27:30.190 --> 27:33.100
Do you know if he had
any immediate family?

27:33.193 --> 27:35.403
He did mention that he had a son.

27:35.404 --> 27:38.364
Well, he decided to make
you his beneficiary.

27:38.365 --> 27:40.274
What's up?

27:42.119 --> 27:45.246
I admit, it seems strange to
me too, but he was insistent.

27:45.247 --> 27:48.541
- I didn't know this man.
- Don't get too upset.

27:48.542 --> 27:54.881
It would appear to me that you've made
out very well in this transaction.

27:54.882 --> 27:59.093
Pink slip to his car. He
signed it over to you.

27:59.094 --> 28:02.505
- He left me his car?
- And that's not all.

28:03.432 --> 28:07.685
He asked only one thing. That you take
care of the expenses of his burial.

28:07.686 --> 28:09.479
Of course.

28:09.480 --> 28:12.857
You'll be notified when
we release the body.

28:12.858 --> 28:15.735
Ordinarily in a homicide,

28:15.736 --> 28:18.446
we're supposed to fill
out a police report,

28:18.447 --> 28:21.074
turn over personal effects
to the authorities.

28:21.075 --> 28:25.286
But, you know, that
can get complicated.

28:25.287 --> 28:27.238
Of course.

28:29.750 --> 28:33.452
Very well. Glad we got
this straightened out.

30:17.107 --> 30:19.734
What do we say when
someone gives us a present?

30:19.735 --> 30:23.521
- Thank you, Daddy.
- That's right, baby.

30:24.448 --> 30:27.909
All right, sugar.
Now it's your turn.

30:27.910 --> 30:30.244
You like that, huh?

30:30.245 --> 30:32.580
Don't give you no cavities, either.

30:32.581 --> 30:35.717
Saves some money on
those dentist bills.

30:36.418 --> 30:38.786
You know what I'm saying?

30:41.173 --> 30:48.012
Daddy got something hard for both y'all,
but it ain't candy. You wanna see it?

30:48.013 --> 30:51.641
- Who the fuck is that?
- It's important.

30:51.642 --> 30:54.435
Shit, better be important.

30:54.436 --> 30:56.721
Be right back, baby.

31:01.985 --> 31:06.113
- Rockie, what's up, man?
- I just got word from the hospital.

31:06.114 --> 31:10.568
- David passed, ten past seven.
- That's good.

31:10.619 --> 31:14.330
Somebody took him there.
Left him in the car.

31:14.331 --> 31:17.658
- Now, what if David talked?
- Who?

31:18.460 --> 31:21.912
- A white kid.
- White kid.

31:22.589 --> 31:24.832
Make some calls and
handle it for me.

31:38.238 --> 31:42.108
It's Mom. How'd your big job
interview go? Did you get it?

31:43.193 --> 31:48.239
Hey, it's Nancy. We're still on for
tonight, right? Give me a call, OK? Bye.

31:49.324 --> 31:52.034
Mr. Paskoff, this is Phillip
Waters, Sun-Telegram.

31:52.035 --> 31:55.788
I hope I didn't give you the wrong
impression in our meeting today.

31:55.789 --> 31:57.873
Your writing samples are topnotch

31:57.874 --> 32:03.004
and I'm genuinely interested in seeing what
kind of story you can come up with for us.

32:03.005 --> 32:05.581
I'll see you on Friday.

32:35.495 --> 32:38.239
The Autobiography of a King.

32:38.290 --> 32:41.242
Chapter one, "Getaway."

32:42.419 --> 32:45.579
Today is the first day
of the rest of my life.

32:45.589 --> 32:48.007
Copped my stash from Moon.

32:48.008 --> 32:51.510
Now it's time to wave goodbye
to that motherfucker.

32:51.511 --> 32:54.555
I was gonna stick around
till Mother's Day.

32:54.556 --> 32:57.850
Figured some of my bitches would
have some extra cash for a nigga.

32:57.851 --> 33:01.771
You know, along with those
government cheques.

33:01.772 --> 33:05.307
That stupid bitch
Edna fucked that up.

33:06.068 --> 33:10.696
Had to make the phone call,
screaming her fucking head off.

33:10.697 --> 33:14.942
Well, you know. Shit happens.

33:17.079 --> 33:20.531
Anyway, plan's still on track.

33:21.750 --> 33:27.621
Three long months of footwork for Moon,
slowly gaining his trust, finally paid off.

33:28.840 --> 33:32.093
Got him to front me a half
a brick on consignment.

33:32.094 --> 33:34.261
Dummy.

33:34.262 --> 33:37.139
What the fuck was
that nigga thinking?

33:37.140 --> 33:40.476
Definitely not what I
was thinking. You know?

33:40.477 --> 33:42.103
Whoa, hold it.

33:42.104 --> 33:46.607
Moon will be looking for a nigga.
No doubt about that.

33:46.608 --> 33:49.777
And I'm sure the pigs are
gonna be on my ass too,

33:49.778 --> 33:53.781
thanks to my little
misunderstanding with Edna.

33:53.782 --> 33:57.818
But fuck you, and good
luck trying to find me.

34:04.084 --> 34:06.544
Everything's been building
up to this point.

34:06.545 --> 34:11.632
Getting out of this hellhole,
reinventing myself.

34:11.632 --> 34:14.918
LA, here I come.

34:18.014 --> 34:21.684
Whoever said there was no such
thing as a second chance in life

34:21.685 --> 34:24.145
was a stupid motherfucker.

34:24.146 --> 34:26.856
This is America.

34:26.857 --> 34:30.484
All you need is a dream and
the will to make it happen.

34:33.155 --> 34:35.322
It feels good, having
a clean slate.

34:35.322 --> 34:38.492
Got the world on the half shell
with lemon and hot sauce.

34:38.493 --> 34:41.996
Folks out here better get ready.
They ain't gonna know what...

34:44.373 --> 34:45.498
Hello?

34:45.500 --> 34:47.333
- You're still there?
- Hey, Nancy.

34:47.335 --> 34:51.045
I know it's our anniversary. You
won't believe what I experienced.

34:51.047 --> 34:55.217
- You're still at work. I'm not complaining.
- I'm waiting for you to pick me up!

34:55.217 --> 34:57.150
You know what? I
don't wanna hear it.

34:57.177 --> 34:59.847
I'm sorry. I'll explain
it all when I get there.

34:59.848 --> 35:03.926
How stupid that I
even listened to you.

35:05.395 --> 35:06.729
Rockie.

35:06.730 --> 35:09.190
- You heard anything?
- Not a word.

35:09.191 --> 35:13.394
Jesus Christ. Ain't this
a bitch? Goddamn!

35:15.113 --> 35:17.198
This shit is fucked up.

35:17.199 --> 35:21.619
I got plans, me and the twins, to go hear
this singer I'm thinking about signing.

35:21.620 --> 35:25.539
- Then all this shit with Mike.
- So how you wanna play it, boss?

35:25.540 --> 35:31.837
If that bastard Mike is breathing out
there, anywhere, I want him taken care of.

35:31.838 --> 35:36.091
And the white boy witness motherfucker,
I want him taken care of too.

35:36.092 --> 35:40.054
I cannot have this shit come back
and bite me in my goddamn ass.

35:40.055 --> 35:46.727
Everything I worked for, everything can
come tumbling down on our fucking heads.

35:46.728 --> 35:50.431
Shit. You're running
shit, handle it.

36:26.601 --> 36:29.603
This is Mike. Leave a message.
I'll get back to you.

37:37.255 --> 37:40.341
- You didn't go to the police?
- Please, Nancy, keep it down.

37:40.342 --> 37:42.709
No, I will not keep it down.

37:42.761 --> 37:46.263
A pimp bled to death in that thing

37:46.264 --> 37:48.807
and you're acting like
everything's just fine and dandy.

37:48.808 --> 37:51.051
I can't explain it.

37:53.229 --> 37:57.349
If you just could have been
there. He had this nobility.

37:57.359 --> 37:58.943
Nobility?

37:58.944 --> 38:02.196
I need to find out
why this man died.

38:02.197 --> 38:05.407
- For my story.
- For your story?

38:05.408 --> 38:08.077
Do you even hear
what you're saying?

38:08.078 --> 38:12.206
This is not a rap video or a
Quentin Tarantino movie, Paul.

38:12.207 --> 38:15.709
This is real life. Your life.

38:15.710 --> 38:19.338
Your whole slumming thing, you
staying uptown in that hellhole,

38:19.339 --> 38:22.883
when you could be living down here
with me, I've put up with it, I have.

38:22.884 --> 38:26.595
- That's a cheap shot, Nancy.
- What? Slumming?

38:26.596 --> 38:29.056
I'm sorry, I forgot.
You're a serious artist,

38:29.057 --> 38:33.102
injecting yourself into an exotic
milieu for research purposes, right?

38:33.103 --> 38:36.146
Isn't that how you once put it?

38:36.147 --> 38:40.184
So, what? Is dating me a
part of your research?

38:47.701 --> 38:50.485
Call me when you get a life.

39:11.391 --> 39:15.052
Snatched up a little
crib near the beach.

39:20.483 --> 39:24.653
Figured I'd check shit out for a
few days before setting up shop.

39:24.654 --> 39:27.898
See if I could make
some connections.

40:30.345 --> 40:33.964
I made a connection, all right.

40:34.891 --> 40:38.635
Mmm-mmm.

40:45.276 --> 40:48.562
So, you ready to go again?

40:48.571 --> 40:53.567
- Are you?
- Mmm-hmm. Yeah.

40:53.576 --> 40:55.902
Her name was Janet.

40:56.830 --> 40:59.164
I ain't been in Cali but 24 hours

40:59.165 --> 41:03.585
and already copped me a white broad that
looked like a motherfucking movie star.

41:03.586 --> 41:06.672
Or TV, anyway.

41:06.673 --> 41:09.842
The show is called SurfBeat.

41:09.843 --> 41:11.844
My character's Pepper.

41:11.845 --> 41:15.722
She's the scatterbrained
but lovable associate

41:15.723 --> 41:18.725
at the Zuma Beach Detective Agency.

41:18.726 --> 41:24.523
- Gotta be serious money in that.
- It's not as good as it sounds, sweetie.

41:24.524 --> 41:28.235
It's just cable and
it's only recurring.

41:28.236 --> 41:31.321
Oh! Watch out, watch
out, watch out.

41:31.322 --> 41:34.658
- Those new shoes you got.
- I know.

41:34.659 --> 41:37.361
Can we go back to the hotel
and do some more blow?

41:45.253 --> 41:48.088
Damn, David.

41:48.089 --> 41:51.133
This is strong. Maybe
you ought to cut it.

41:51.134 --> 41:55.262
That stupid bitch didn't even know the
difference between coke and heroin.

41:55.263 --> 41:59.091
Fuck, it's all I had. And I didn't
have the heart to tell her.

42:00.268 --> 42:03.470
Oh, well. She'd find
out eventually.

42:03.938 --> 42:06.681
They always do.

42:07.066 --> 42:10.644
Within a few weeks,
business was booming.

42:11.946 --> 42:15.449
Everybody wanted
what I had to offer.

42:15.450 --> 42:19.486
I didn't even have to act like it
was coke no more. As for Janet...

42:24.292 --> 42:28.670
Cut! Cut, cut, cut! Let's
do another one, please.

42:28.671 --> 42:30.497
She wasn't doing too hot.

42:30.548 --> 42:33.959
What's the matter, honey? You can't
seem to get any energy going.

42:36.471 --> 42:38.922
Hey! We need you for this shot.

42:38.973 --> 42:41.675
- She still had her job, though.
- Asshole.

42:43.770 --> 42:47.139
Yo. Janet had it bad.

42:48.024 --> 42:49.983
But I took care of her.

42:49.984 --> 42:56.815
After all, she was really good about
hooking me up with her co-workers.

43:02.830 --> 43:06.333
Sometimes I'd get a kick out of just
watching the show and wondering

43:06.334 --> 43:10.379
if the rest of the world could tell which
members of the cast were strung out.

43:10.380 --> 43:13.006
Just looking at them
motherfuckers made me laugh.

43:13.007 --> 43:16.376
Cos I knew I could bring their
whole world crumbling down

43:16.386 --> 43:18.753
whenever I felt like
pulling the string.

43:21.641 --> 43:25.760
- You're a fucking asshole.
- Yeah, but you can't live without me.

43:25.853 --> 43:28.313
Oh, really?

43:28.314 --> 43:32.567
I used to think your living in LA for too
long would give you a big head, David.

43:32.568 --> 43:37.531
- Thank God I was wrong.
- But what would you do without me?

43:37.532 --> 43:40.066
Whatever.

43:42.370 --> 43:43.862
You'll see.

43:45.123 --> 43:48.074
Oh, yeah. She'd definitely see.

44:00.930 --> 44:03.473
- We're closed, man.
- My window's busted.

44:03.474 --> 44:06.635
- You're the only garage around.
- Sorry.

44:07.562 --> 44:10.105
I'll make it worth your while.

44:10.106 --> 44:13.433
OK. I'll get you a ticket.

46:10.017 --> 46:11.968
What's the password?

46:16.023 --> 46:19.151
- Put that thing down, man.
- Mike, Moon's not here.

46:19.152 --> 46:22.195
- Where is he?
- Don't go out like that, my brother.

46:22.196 --> 46:24.281
Mike, me and you, we'll
work something out.

46:24.282 --> 46:27.651
What are we gonna work out, Rock?

46:28.744 --> 46:30.362
Ella's gone.

46:32.540 --> 46:34.866
She's gone?

46:37.211 --> 46:38.828
Where is he?

46:39.464 --> 46:40.755
By now,

46:40.756 --> 46:44.509
I'd pretty much burned through
the stash I copped from Moon.

46:44.510 --> 46:49.339
Those entertainment types
in LA are fiends. Who knew?

46:49.390 --> 46:53.810
It was a good ride.
I cleared 25Gs easy.

46:53.811 --> 46:57.564
But if I was to keep this shit going,
I'd need to do some re-ing up.

46:57.565 --> 47:00.016
Make myself a West
Coast connection.

47:01.068 --> 47:03.603
Easier said than done.

47:06.407 --> 47:08.700
Who could guess a
two-bit chump like Moon

47:08.701 --> 47:11.244
would have better dope
than anybody in LA?

47:11.245 --> 47:16.583
I guess the real junkies, the ones who
know their shit, are all back East.

47:16.584 --> 47:18.668
They're scared of the sunshine.

47:18.669 --> 47:21.588
Way I see it, though, that
means a golden opportunity

47:21.589 --> 47:26.626
for anybody out here who could
provide some quality shit.

47:27.887 --> 47:30.972
Yep, ain't no doubt about it.

47:30.973 --> 47:35.101
Heroin is definitely an industry
with some serious growth potential.

47:35.102 --> 47:38.304
And I planned to invest heavily.

47:38.606 --> 47:42.267
Eventually, I hooked up with some
Vietnamese cats out in Alhambra.

47:42.276 --> 47:45.570
I hear brothers screaming about
dirty gook motherfuckers.

47:45.571 --> 47:50.108
Say what you want, them motherfuckers
know how to conduct business.

47:52.453 --> 47:58.667
Janet could've learned a thing or two
about a thing or two from them. For real.

48:00.127 --> 48:03.037
- Just a minute.
- No. Now!

48:08.135 --> 48:10.178
This is David. Leave it.

48:10.179 --> 48:13.659
Hi, David. It's me. I don't
give a fuck where you are.

48:13.661 --> 48:18.511
Please, it's a fucking emergency.
I ran out, OK? So, please...

48:19.438 --> 48:23.483
I really need you, OK?
So call me back.

48:27.488 --> 48:29.781
- You know the bitch lost her job.
- Sorry.

48:29.782 --> 48:31.700
Right before the third season.

48:31.701 --> 48:36.037
Had the nerve to blame me. Like I
had something to do with that shit.

48:36.038 --> 48:37.914
And me?

48:37.915 --> 48:40.533
I wound up losing interest.

48:44.463 --> 48:46.673
She found herself a new job.

48:46.674 --> 48:49.501
It paid the bills.

48:55.766 --> 48:59.177
Left me with time to
focus on other things.

49:18.789 --> 49:21.916
I'd buy you a drink but you
probably get 'em on the house.

49:21.917 --> 49:25.837
Gee, I never heard that one before.

49:25.838 --> 49:27.789
What's your name, girl?

49:28.799 --> 49:30.041
Busy.

49:32.595 --> 49:34.921
- I'm so sorry.
- Don't worry about it.

49:34.930 --> 49:37.599
It's only vodka. Won't stain.

49:37.600 --> 49:41.353
- So, what's your name?
- Look, I'm sorry but I'm really busy.

49:41.354 --> 49:43.146
I mean, come on. Looking
as good as you do?

49:43.147 --> 49:44.639
I just wanna know your name.

49:45.733 --> 49:48.735
- Juanita.
- Pretty name.

49:48.736 --> 49:50.987
I'm David. My friends call me King.

49:50.988 --> 49:53.907
Oh, let me guess. You're
looking for a queen?

49:53.908 --> 49:56.710
You don't cut a brother
no slack, do you?

49:56.911 --> 50:02.248
Well, you know, we meet a lot of creeps in
here. Look, sorry again about your drink.

50:02.249 --> 50:05.585
How about you let me take you
out to dinner this weekend?

50:05.586 --> 50:08.046
Oh, I can't. I'm studying.

50:08.047 --> 50:14.010
Oh, college girl. I should've guessed.
You don't really fit in with this crowd.

50:14.011 --> 50:18.014
- How about next weekend?
- Midterms.

50:18.015 --> 50:20.934
- Can I call?
- I'll tell you what.

50:20.935 --> 50:26.272
I'm working next Thursday. Come back
and ask me then and we'll see. OK?

50:26.273 --> 50:29.893
- I'll do that.
- Now, if you'll excuse me.

50:31.904 --> 50:38.785
She was everything a man could want.
Beautiful, intelligent, uncorrupted.

50:38.786 --> 50:44.157
I promised myself right then
and there she'd be mine.

50:54.969 --> 50:58.004
I'll be right back.
I gotta hit the head.

51:38.262 --> 51:39.963
Shit.

51:42.516 --> 51:44.309
Who the fuck is this?

51:44.310 --> 51:47.896
Oh. It's OK, Jasper.
You didn't know.

51:47.897 --> 51:50.106
What's going on?

51:50.107 --> 51:54.310
Now, slow down, slow down.
Give it to me again.

51:55.946 --> 51:58.231
I'm on it. It's all good.

51:59.116 --> 52:01.401
OK.

52:01.994 --> 52:05.488
Give me a second.
This is business, OK?

52:10.419 --> 52:12.045
- Yeah? Uh-huh.
- Yo, Larry.

52:12.046 --> 52:13.880
- You at Mike's?
- Uh-huh.

52:13.881 --> 52:15.840
- Did he show?
- No. No sign of him.

52:15.841 --> 52:17.467
I need you to go down
to the Blue Room.

52:17.468 --> 52:20.804
That white boy's there.
Make him disappear.

52:20.805 --> 52:23.089
All right.

53:10.479 --> 53:15.558
It's on the house, honey. Don't
go nowhere. I'll be right back.

53:20.447 --> 53:22.607
Wait. Wait!

53:26.036 --> 53:27.695
Hey, J!

53:50.811 --> 53:52.979
You already missed him. Nice going.

53:52.980 --> 53:55.648
- Where the fuck did he go?
- How should I know?

53:55.649 --> 54:00.111
He's the only white boy around here and
he's driving around in a pimped-out Stutz.

54:00.112 --> 54:02.355
He shouldn't be that hard to find.

54:18.172 --> 54:22.166
Thursday came, and not
a moment too soon.

54:23.177 --> 54:27.213
Operation Juanita
was in full effect.

54:33.896 --> 54:36.022
Again, girl? Who they from?

54:36.023 --> 54:37.857
Shh.

54:37.858 --> 54:40.685
What does it say?

54:43.822 --> 54:45.281
After I finish this semester,

54:45.282 --> 54:48.534
I plan to stay on and get my
graduate's degree in social work.

54:48.535 --> 54:51.079
You know, help out
disadvantaged children.

54:51.080 --> 54:55.208
It's important to
give back, you know?

54:55.209 --> 54:57.210
I think we should check the car.

54:57.211 --> 54:59.545
You might have left your
halo on the back seat.

54:59.546 --> 55:01.589
Are you making fun of me now?

55:01.590 --> 55:05.051
You're not like any other
girl I've ever dated before.

55:05.052 --> 55:08.930
You're a strong sister. Ambitious.

55:08.931 --> 55:14.352
- But I know what your weakness is.
- Really? OK, well, I'm all ears.

55:14.353 --> 55:17.680
Same thing make you
laugh, make you cry.

55:19.441 --> 55:22.894
Your strength is your weakness.

55:23.278 --> 55:26.856
Turns out that wasn't her only one.

55:27.741 --> 55:30.067
Shit.

55:32.246 --> 55:34.572
David!

55:37.376 --> 55:40.586
- Can I try some?
- Sure.

55:40.587 --> 55:44.757
Guess there ain't a bitch alive who don't
like a little coke every now and then.

55:44.758 --> 55:47.844
Makes them kinda freaky too.

55:47.845 --> 55:52.048
Truth be told, they were
freaks to begin with.

57:04.379 --> 57:06.881
What's this?

57:06.882 --> 57:11.085
I think it's about time
you got your own place.

57:12.012 --> 57:15.214
You're breaking up with me?

57:18.310 --> 57:19.727
- David.
- You gonna help?

57:19.728 --> 57:23.055
Or stand there talking
about "David, David?"

57:27.694 --> 57:30.863
- What's her name?
- Does it matter?

57:30.864 --> 57:33.658
She moving in here with you?

57:33.659 --> 57:37.611
You know, I haven't asked her yet.
But I'm hoping she will.

57:46.421 --> 57:48.581
You must really like her.

57:53.053 --> 57:56.514
Guess I can't say I
didn't see this coming.

57:56.515 --> 57:59.925
