01:05:08.446 --> 01:05:11.190
Oh, shit. Get my phone.

01:05:11.992 --> 01:05:13.233
Shit.

01:05:19.249 --> 01:05:21.792
Hello?

01:05:21.793 --> 01:05:25.963
Motherfucker's hung up. All right,
bitch, tell me another joke.

01:05:29.092 --> 01:05:31.293
Mike. Son.

01:06:16.556 --> 01:06:19.725
- Yeah?
- Hey, Moon.

01:06:19.726 --> 01:06:25.806
They spotted the white boy at the garage.
We followed him north on Fifth Street.

01:06:29.444 --> 01:06:30.903
Responsibility.

01:06:30.904 --> 01:06:32.604
Redemption.

01:06:32.614 --> 01:06:37.776
In order to be truly redeemed, a man
has to own up to his responsibilities.

01:06:40.955 --> 01:06:43.540
Tuesday, moving day.

01:06:43.541 --> 01:06:46.785
It didn't have to come to this
but the bitch left me no choice.

01:06:48.338 --> 01:06:51.006
Three months of planning
had finally paid off.

01:06:51.007 --> 01:06:54.793
Unfortunately, a little too well.

01:06:58.098 --> 01:07:01.975
You bastard. Why haven't
you been returning my calls?

01:07:01.976 --> 01:07:06.355
- I went out of town, man. I didn't tell you?
- No, you didn't tell me.

01:07:06.356 --> 01:07:09.942
- Aren't you gonna open the door?
- Not if you continue in that tone of voice.

01:07:09.943 --> 01:07:13.645
- Open the fucking door!
- Try asking nicely.

01:07:14.823 --> 01:07:17.441
Please!

01:07:22.914 --> 01:07:24.957
So, what seems to be the problem?

01:07:24.958 --> 01:07:28.669
You know damn well what the
problem is. You did this to me.

01:07:28.670 --> 01:07:32.840
I did this to you? I didn't put a gun to
your head and make you sniff no coke.

01:07:32.841 --> 01:07:37.461
You didn't give me coke,
you fucker. You gave me heroin.

01:07:37.554 --> 01:07:39.838
That's right. I did.

01:07:42.851 --> 01:07:44.343
So, what do you want me to do?

01:07:46.896 --> 01:07:49.148
Baby, I just need a fix.

01:07:49.149 --> 01:07:53.068
Look, just for today, OK? You know?
Just to get me through it. Please?

01:07:53.069 --> 01:07:54.778
- Right.
- Just one, OK?

01:07:54.779 --> 01:07:58.490
Yeah. But you know us small-timers.

01:07:58.491 --> 01:08:02.828
You know, we gots to
watch every penny, and...

01:08:02.829 --> 01:08:05.906
Don't look like you have a penny.

01:08:06.791 --> 01:08:10.035
You're enjoying this, aren't you?

01:08:15.508 --> 01:08:17.676
She was right.

01:08:17.676 --> 01:08:20.261
I did do this to her.

01:08:20.263 --> 01:08:22.546
And I was enjoying it.

01:08:23.349 --> 01:08:25.267
Funny shit was,

01:08:25.268 --> 01:08:27.810
I still loved her.

01:08:27.812 --> 01:08:30.389
Maybe more now than ever.

01:08:30.398 --> 01:08:34.017
Because I finally felt
needed, appreciated.

01:08:45.287 --> 01:08:47.738
Come on back, any time.

01:08:49.542 --> 01:08:54.371
Thing is, Juanita got more strung out
than I ever could have imagined.

01:08:54.380 --> 01:08:56.756
Bitch started shooting right away.

01:08:56.758 --> 01:09:00.426
Most girls are scared of needles.
Keeps it from getting out of control.

01:09:00.428 --> 01:09:03.839
Not Juanita. Turns out
she was diabetic.

01:09:05.308 --> 01:09:11.304
For her, sticking herself was like brushing
her teeth or going to the bathroom.

01:09:12.732 --> 01:09:19.770
It don't take a rocket scientist to figure
out that eventually something had to give.

01:09:36.714 --> 01:09:40.917
- Yeah?
- I need help.

01:09:41.386 --> 01:09:43.492
Look, there's a clinic up north.

01:09:43.493 --> 01:09:47.198
It's the best in the state
and I wanna check myself in.

01:09:47.934 --> 01:09:51.303
But it's expensive. 10,000 a month.

01:09:52.939 --> 01:09:57.025
And I know it's a lot of
money, but I need this.

01:09:57.026 --> 01:09:59.444
You have to help me.

01:09:59.445 --> 01:10:02.614
If you don't, I'll
go to the police.

01:10:02.615 --> 01:10:06.118
Bitches don't realize they should
never joke about the police.

01:10:06.119 --> 01:10:08.036
Breaking a man's
heart is one thing.

01:10:08.037 --> 01:10:10.747
Fucking with his livelihood
is something else.

01:10:10.748 --> 01:10:16.336
I knew you'd see things my way.
I'll meet you at eight.

01:10:16.337 --> 01:10:21.383
I wonder how she felt inside after hanging
up that phone, what was on her mind.

01:10:21.384 --> 01:10:23.552
Like the sunset that day.

01:10:23.553 --> 01:10:26.638
Do you think it occurred
to her for a split second

01:10:26.639 --> 01:10:29.841
that it was the last one
she was ever gonna see?

01:10:33.479 --> 01:10:37.774
You know that thing Yogi Berra used
to say, "Déjà vu all over again?"

01:10:37.775 --> 01:10:39.776
Might as well been
talking about me.

01:10:39.777 --> 01:10:42.279
Here I am trying to resolve
things with Juanita,

01:10:42.280 --> 01:10:44.406
and it's just like the mess
I'd gotten myself into

01:10:44.407 --> 01:10:47.701
the day I left the
East Coast, with Edna.

01:10:47.702 --> 01:10:50.547
I mean it, King. I need money.

01:10:50.549 --> 01:10:52.956
For what? So you can shoot
it in your fucking veins?

01:10:52.957 --> 01:10:56.001
I told you, I'm clean now.

01:10:56.002 --> 01:10:58.295
Six weeks.

01:10:58.296 --> 01:10:59.796
I've heard that one before.

01:10:59.797 --> 01:11:02.799
Now, you think I like
asking you for money?

01:11:02.800 --> 01:11:08.421
There's no food in the house.
The kids need clothes for school.

01:11:10.141 --> 01:11:13.385
You know, you owe this to me.

01:11:18.691 --> 01:11:20.108
I'll go to the police.

01:11:20.109 --> 01:11:22.945
Wait a minute, wait a
minute, wait a minute.

01:11:22.946 --> 01:11:25.230
Don't do that.

01:11:27.742 --> 01:11:29.401
I'll be right over.

01:11:30.954 --> 01:11:35.248
Edna. Yeah, I used to run around
with her back in the day.

01:11:35.249 --> 01:11:38.377
Bad-ass bitch before that
junk got hold of her.

01:11:38.378 --> 01:11:42.047
Somehow she got it in her head
that I was the father of her boy

01:11:42.048 --> 01:11:47.419
and conveniently waited till now, ten years
after the fact, to break the news to me.

01:11:47.512 --> 01:11:50.722
Maybe I was, maybe I wasn't.

01:11:50.723 --> 01:11:54.059
But she wasn't gonna do her kids
any good if she was still using.

01:11:54.060 --> 01:11:58.313
And I sure as hell wasn't gonna do
them any good rotting in a jail cell.

01:11:58.314 --> 01:12:00.732
So I decided to give her a test,

01:12:00.733 --> 01:12:03.727
to see if she was on the level.

01:12:06.656 --> 01:12:08.865
Well, aren't you gonna let me in?

01:12:08.866 --> 01:12:12.744
- I'm glad you came.
- So am I.

01:12:12.745 --> 01:12:16.281
I'm sure we can work
this thing out.

01:12:18.835 --> 01:12:22.120
- Got something to drink?
- Yeah, go ahead. Help yourself.

01:12:25.049 --> 01:12:28.335
You ain't got nothing to
eat in this motherfucker.

01:12:30.430 --> 01:12:34.799
You mind? I don't want to eat
you out of house and home.

01:12:39.897 --> 01:12:42.766
Damn.

01:12:42.775 --> 01:12:45.694
It is hotter than a
motherfucker out there.

01:12:45.695 --> 01:12:48.563
David, I need help.

01:12:54.537 --> 01:12:58.123
Baby. You ain't gots to
be like that with me.

01:12:58.124 --> 01:13:03.328
Come here.

01:13:06.049 --> 01:13:10.168
What the fuck is wrong with you,
threatening to call the police on me, bitch?

01:13:11.387 --> 01:13:15.590
- You out of your motherfucking mind.
- Leave her alone!

01:13:16.809 --> 01:13:19.803
- Get out of here, little nigga.
- Leave him alone.

01:13:21.731 --> 01:13:24.015
Look at you.

01:13:25.568 --> 01:13:28.311
This what you want the money for?

01:13:29.447 --> 01:13:31.398
You better enjoy it.

01:13:31.491 --> 01:13:34.693
It's the last thing you're
getting from me, boo.

01:13:35.119 --> 01:13:36.987
Get the fuck out of my way.

01:13:44.337 --> 01:13:48.131
Didn't stick around long enough to
see if she ever did pass that test.

01:13:48.132 --> 01:13:52.919
What I did was hit the airport.
Got me a one-way to LA.

01:14:20.289 --> 01:14:22.574
Mom!

01:14:25.002 --> 01:14:27.254
Mommy. Mommy!

01:14:27.255 --> 01:14:31.207
Mommy! Mommy! Mommy!

01:14:39.350 --> 01:14:42.135
Aren't you gonna let me in?

01:14:46.065 --> 01:14:48.150
Déjà vu.

01:14:48.151 --> 01:14:50.435
All over again.

01:15:08.087 --> 01:15:11.590
I drifted around for a
while, ducking the law.

01:15:11.591 --> 01:15:14.959
Worked my way East from
small town to small town.

01:15:15.011 --> 01:15:18.763
But something was calling
me back. I missed my home.

01:15:18.764 --> 01:15:22.684
Plus it's hard living on the run,
especially when it's your fault.

01:15:22.685 --> 01:15:25.478
Getting yourself stuck in the
same fucked-up situation

01:15:25.479 --> 01:15:28.273
you ran away from ten years ago.

01:15:28.274 --> 01:15:32.068
The Lord takes care of fools and
babies. I've never been either one.

01:15:32.069 --> 01:15:35.325
So I'm back, and it's time for
King to put things right,

01:15:35.327 --> 01:15:40.285
face up to my responsibilities, to
Moon, to Edna's boy, to myself.

01:15:40.286 --> 01:15:43.246
Responsibility. Redemption.

01:15:43.247 --> 01:15:46.041
In order to be truly be
redeemed, a man has to...

01:15:46.042 --> 01:15:48.919
Get out the car! Get out the
motherfucking car, white boy.

01:15:48.920 --> 01:15:50.879
Get out the motherfucking car.

01:15:50.880 --> 01:15:53.173
- Get out the car now!
- OK.

01:15:53.174 --> 01:15:55.133
- Do it now!
- All right.

01:15:55.134 --> 01:15:58.211
- Get out the car!
- Please don't kill me!

01:16:00.139 --> 01:16:04.851
Motherfucker, I'm gonna count
to three. One. Two. Three.

01:16:13.694 --> 01:16:17.313
Don't come near me!
I'll kill you! I mean it!

01:16:26.332 --> 01:16:32.420
You. If you're worried about me going
to the police, I didn't, I swear.

01:16:32.421 --> 01:16:37.876
I don't care about that. Now, put the
gun down. I ain't gonna hurt you.

01:16:44.016 --> 01:16:47.760
- What's your name?
- Paul.

01:16:47.853 --> 01:16:51.389
What the fuck is a white boy like you
doing uptown in a dead man's car, Paul?

01:16:53.234 --> 01:16:56.478
He gave it to me before he died.

01:16:56.487 --> 01:16:58.897
He give you that ring too?

01:17:01.951 --> 01:17:05.236
Take your ass home, man.
You don't belong here.

01:17:05.246 --> 01:17:07.530
I need to know why.

01:17:12.336 --> 01:17:15.914
- Why what?
- Why did you kill him?

01:17:15.965 --> 01:17:20.460
- He deserved it.
- Believe me, I know.

01:17:21.721 --> 01:17:24.255
But why'd you kill him?

01:17:33.941 --> 01:17:36.434
He killed my mother.

01:17:37.903 --> 01:17:39.312
Edna?

01:17:43.075 --> 01:17:45.902
The man that you killed

01:17:47.580 --> 01:17:50.240
was your father.

01:17:53.794 --> 01:17:57.205
You see, he has these tapes of...

01:17:58.382 --> 01:18:01.626
I've been listening to 'em.

01:18:02.887 --> 01:18:07.257
See, when he was dying,
he asked me to bury him.

01:18:15.941 --> 01:18:18.810
He begged for a decent burial.

01:18:19.820 --> 01:18:22.105
Hallowed ground.

01:18:25.117 --> 01:18:28.578
Oh! Man.

01:18:28.579 --> 01:18:32.374
Hurry. Come on. You
gotta get out of here.

01:18:32.375 --> 01:18:37.253
Take the car. There's a quarter-million
dollars in the trunk. It's yours.

01:18:37.254 --> 01:18:38.713
You're free. Go!

01:18:38.714 --> 01:18:40.790
Get out of here! Go!

01:18:46.347 --> 01:18:48.631
Go.

01:19:20.756 --> 01:19:23.299
An amazing story.

01:19:23.300 --> 01:19:25.385
Truly amazing.

01:19:25.386 --> 01:19:27.846
- But I can't print it.
- Why not?

01:19:27.847 --> 01:19:30.298
This is a newspaper,
not a fiction magazine.

01:19:30.307 --> 01:19:31.883
But it's true, all of it.

01:19:31.892 --> 01:19:35.386
The stabbing, the hospital.
I had a gun pointed at my head.

01:19:37.481 --> 01:19:41.225
You're a great writer. If it's
a job you want, you're hired.

01:19:41.527 --> 01:19:43.770
But that?

01:19:46.907 --> 01:19:50.818
Unfortunately, I don't
believe a word of it.

01:19:50.995 --> 01:19:56.082
Tell you the truth, I probably
wouldn't have believed it, either.

01:19:56.083 --> 01:20:01.704
After all, I did live a
pretty extraordinary life.

01:20:01.839 --> 01:20:06.334
It's too bad it had to catch
up with me when it did.

01:20:06.510 --> 01:20:10.088
Before I had a chance
to turn the corner.

01:20:12.725 --> 01:20:15.718
And write the final chapter.

01:20:35.581 --> 01:20:37.448
Fate's a funny thing,

01:20:37.541 --> 01:20:40.118
when you think about it.

01:20:44.089 --> 01:20:49.293
How everything is interconnected,
like a game of dominoes.

01:20:57.686 --> 01:21:00.438
How one man's life can have
such a powerful effect,

01:21:00.439 --> 01:21:04.142
however inadvertent, on the
lives of so many others.

01:21:09.615 --> 01:21:15.319
How it can transform itself into
a gift that keeps on giving.

01:21:24.255 --> 01:21:25.922
Like I said,

01:21:25.923 --> 01:21:30.134
I guess my life was
pretty extraordinary.

01:21:30.135 --> 01:21:36.140
In the end, I suppose it all comes
back to the whole karma thing.

01:21:36.141 --> 01:21:38.476
Who knows?

01:21:38.477 --> 01:21:41.563
If it's half as real
as the Hindus say,

01:21:41.564 --> 01:21:45.308
I may just get a second
chance after all.

01:21:46.235 --> 01:21:48.444
I wonder.

01:21:48.445 --> 01:21:51.689
What lies ahead for
me on the other side?

